str2: For. A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason.
Not yet. From me and po; not yet.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Passive - Genitive Masculine Plural
str2: From a variation of genos; to procreate; figuratively, to regenerate.
And not, not even, neither?nor. From me and de; but not, not even; in a continued negation, nor.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Genitive Masculine Plural
str2: To do, perform, accomplish; be in any condition, i.e. I fare; I exact, require.

parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Accusative Neuter Singular
str2: Any one, some one, a certain one or thing. An enclitic indefinite pronoun; some or any person or object.
Or, than. A primary particle of distinction between two connected terms; disjunctive, or; comparative, than.
Worthless, wicked, base. Apparently a primary word; 'foul' or 'flawy', i.e. wicked.
In order that, so that. Probably from the same as the former part of heautou; in order that.
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.
From protithemai; a setting forth, i.e. proposal; specially, the show-bread as exposed before God.
A primary particle; down, in varied relations (genitive, dative or accusative) with which it is joined).
A choosing out, selecting, choice (by God). From eklegomai; selection.

parse: Verb - Present Subjunctive Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To remain, abide, stay, wait; with acc: I wait for, await. A primary verb; to stay.
